Decent Subway outlet serving Subway's standardised menu of choice, including subway sandwiches, sandwich meats, fixings, condiments, and soft drinks. the location has some space outside to afford outdoor eating if the weather appeals. Subway is a take it or leave it place - you know what you are getting, the only question is whether the standard meets the franchise's aspiration. in this case, the answer is yes.

I came here to get a sandwich and they gave me a meat that tasted funny. when I asked for a new sandwich naomi or the what the young lady’s name was refuse to make the sandwich until I started calling the number on the receipt, which was just the number to the store. So then she offered to make a new one but was very rude to me. She said, you need to make sure you get the right meat cause I’m not making another one. At that point I just wanted a refund and she refused to give it to me. I didn’t feel like arguing so I just left, empty handed. When i walked out I called the store and asked for the manager and then was hung up on. I was trying to reach Doris Ramos.
